[src:joi-validation/global-objects-object] These properties are defined on `Object.prototype` and shared by all `Object` instances.
[src:joi-validation/global-objects-object] Points to the object which was used as prototype when the object was instantiated.
[src:joi-validation/global-objects-object] The constructor function that created the instance object.
[src:joi-validation/global-objects-object] For plain `Object` instances, the initial value is the `Object` constructor.
[src:joi-validation/global-objects-object] Instances of other constructors each inherit the `constructor` property from their respective `Constructor.prototype` object.
